					<tr class="SECTION" style="background-color: #ffffff;">
						<td align="left" bgcolor="#ffffff" style="padding: 0 0 0 45px;">
						<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="510">
							<tbody>
								<tr>
									<td>
									<h1 style="mso-table-lspace:0;mso-table-rspace:0;margin:0;font-size:30px;line-height:37px;color:#007DC3;font-weight:900;font-family:'Montserrat','Arial Black','Arial',sans-serif;">Welcome to the Alliance Nursing team! ❤</h1>
									</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<!-- EMAIL COPY STARTS HERE -->
									<td style="height:20px">&nbsp;</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td align="left">
									<p style="font-size:18px;line-height:25px;color:#000000;margin:10px 0 20px;">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br /><br />

Once you have received your uniform and badge we can start booking you for shifts.<br /><br />

Our Recruitment Consultants have advised the Allocations Team today that you are now active for shifts. Excellent news!!<br /><br />

We have attached some important information for you be aware of, I have attached for your convenience the copy of the ‘things to remember page’ you would have received in your orientation and here are a few more details for you to note:<br />

<p style="font-size:18px;line-height:25px;color:#000000;margin:10px 0 20px;">
<ul>
<li>Please ensure to login to the Alliance Portal and ensure all your details are updated including your Tax File Number and your Banking Details. Please also make sure your availability is up to date as this is how the allocations team
 books you for shifts</li><br />
<li>We will be able to start booking you from when you receive your nurse uniform and ID badge – Please let our allocations team know when you have received both these items</li>
-Classifications – I just want to double check your classifications with you to ensure you get the shifts you want. You are happy to work in MH wards only 😊</li><br /><br />
<li>Allocated shifts – when you are allocated shifts in a new facility we will email you all the details we have on file to make it as easy as possible for you such as address, where to report to, how to get there, parking etc. Then
 if you return to the facility in future we will just SMS you confirmation of the exact details e.g. date, time and ward. If you don’t receive these emails or sms’s after we speak to you please call us back.</li><br />
<li>Cancellations – Please ensure you CALL our Allocations team if you ever need to cancel a shift, If you are confirmed for a shift you cannot cancel without a feasible reason Eg. Holidays will not be accepted.</li><br />
<li>Please make sure you have access to the ‘Alliance Connect App’ if you do not have access to this, please let out team know and we can send you an email with instructions to install 😊</li>
</ul>
</p>

<p style="font-size:18px;line-height:25px;color:#000000;margin:10px 0 20px;">And as always, if you have any questions or concerns you can always call our friendly staff on <a href="tel:1300034494">1300 034 494</a><br /><br />
Text only: <a href="tel:0061447037610">+61447037610</a><br /><br />
Email: <a href="mailto:bookings.sydney@alliancenursing.com.au">@Alliance Nursing Bookings - Sydney</a>

<br /><br />We are thrilled to have you onboard!
									<br /><br />
									Kind regards,<br />
									Your team at Alliance Nursing</p>
									</td>
									<!-- EMAIL COPY ENDS HERE -->
								</tr>
